DOM refers to a page.
JS can be used in client as well as server.

Responsibility of in-Browser JS:
1) Add new HTML element and change existing element from DOM.
2) React to events[response from server,keypress,Mouse Movement]. 
3) Ajax requests.
4) Get and Set Cookies & use localStorage.[Storage where we can store data]

What can't in-Browser JS do:
1) Read/Write to & from Computer Hard disk.
2) It follows Same Origin Policy: Cross websites information cannot be extracted.
 but it can access permitted resources.


What makes JavaScript Unique:
1) HTML/CSS Support.
2) Provides us with simple API's like fetch,..
3) Supports Major browsers. 
